<TEXT>
ARES-SERONO, the Swiss pharmaceutical company, said that it expected higher
group net profits for 1992, and added that 1993 earnings should at least
keep pace with 1992 growth, Reuter reports from Zurich. A company
spokeswoman said the group expected 1992 group net profits to rise to more
than Dollars 100m from 1991's Dollars 71.2m. The expected rise was due to
the sale of its non-prescription drugs unit last March to Italy's Home
Products Italiana.
