<HEADLINE>
FT  19 FEB 93 / Ski tour company ceases trading
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
WINTER World, a ski company with 65 groups of customers abroad, has ceased
trading, the Association of British Travel Agents said last night.
The company is an Abta member and clients' money is protected. Abta said it
did not yet know how many skiers were abroad or how many forward bookings
the company had. The company, based in Skipton, North Yorkshire, refused to
comment.
The tour operator Riva Travel was placed in liquidation last night. The
company, which employed failed travel entrepreneur Mr Harry Goodman, as a
consultant, ceased trading last Wednesday. The liquidators are Mr Peter
Souster and Mr Fred Satow of Baker Tilly.
</TEXT>
