<HEADLINE>
FT  19 FEB 93 / World News in Brief: 'Sweet-tooth' tax urged
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Sweets should be taxed as heavily as tobacco and alcohol to raise money for
the treatment of tooth decay, according to the Dental Practitioners
Association, which says the scheme could raise Pounds 1bn.
</TEXT>
<XX>
